Here is what i actioned to get a local Whisper model of my choice setup the way i wanted.

If you use the local setup by default it goes to faster-whisper Huggingface repo.

I wanted to use OpenAI's original Whisper first to get best results before diverging! 

***Notes***
Used ahmetoner/whisper-asr-webservice docker image. 
The main issue is that Open WebUI’s “OpenAI STT” integration expects OpenAI-compatible endpoints, while ahmetoner/whisper-asr-webservice exposes /asr, not the OpenAI-style /v1/audio/transcriptions and /v1/audio/translations routes.
So when Open WebUI is configured as:
Provider: OpenAI
Base URL: http://whisper:9000/v1
Model: whisper-1
it will try to call something like:
POST /v1/audio/transcriptions
but the container i choose only provides:
POST /asr

So thought process was create fastapi in python to change that and make it work!

Planned Architecture:

Open WebUI
     |
     v
OpenAI-compatible proxy
     |
     v
whisper-asr-webservice

