So following work went into it:
```
mkdir ~/whisper-proxy
cd ~/whisper-proxy
nano app.py```

```from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form
import requests

app = FastAPI()

WHISPER_URL = "http://host-gateway:9000/asr"

@app.post("/v1/audio/transcriptions")
async def transcribe(
    file: UploadFile = File(...),
    model: str = Form(...)
):
    files = {
        "audio_file": (
            file.filename,
            await file.read(),
            file.content_type
        )
    }

    r = requests.post(
        f"{WHISPER_URL}?task=transcribe&output=json",
        files=files
    )

    return r.json()


@app.post("/v1/audio/translations")
async def translate(
    file: UploadFile = File(...),
    model: str = Form(...)
):
    files = {
        "audio_file": (
            file.filename,
            await file.read(),
            file.content_type
        )
    }

    r = requests.post(
        f"{WHISPER_URL}?task=translate&output=json",
        files=files
    )

    return r.json()```

nano Dockerfile

```FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app

# Install dependencies
RUN pip install fastapi uvicorn requests python-multipart

# Copy the FastAPI app
COPY app.py .

# Run the app
CMD ["uvicorn", "app:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]```

docker build -t whisper-proxy .


docker run -d \
  --name whisper-proxy \
  --add-host=host-gateway:host-gateway \
  -p 8000:8000 \
  whisper-proxy

Configure Open WebUI

Go to Admin → Audio Settings:
Provider: OpenAI
Base URL: http://host-gateway:8000/v1
API Key: leave blank or put dummy
Model: whisper-1
